      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Hard to rule any of these out. HONEY PERFUME (4) scored two back over this distance at Canberra then stepped up to 1100m at Wyong last start and was less effective. Record at 1000m reads two wins and three minors from six tries. Can bounce back to form in this suitable contest. The danger is AEGIPAN (8) who is back in class on recent runs. Has six career wins to his name and all have come at today's distance. Looks very well treated on 57kgs in this company. BODE AKUNA (1) chimed in late to score over today's journey at Canberra two back. Gave away an impossible start at Wyong last time but really launched late. Major player on this more spacious circuit. TAI LUNG (2) closed well but was never a threat against better opposition at Randwick last time. Penza is two for two on the veteran and he reunites. Certainly in the mix. STORMFIELD (5) is a lightly raced four-year-old with each-way claims first-up from a 16-week spell.",
